        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="pencil"/>[EVENING AT CHAMOUNI.]</head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    
                    <l>NOT such the night whose stormy might</l>
                    <l>Heroic Balmat braved,</l>
                    <l>When, darkening on the Go&#x00FB;t&#x00E9;&#x02BC;s height,</l> 
                    <l>The tempest howled and raved.</l>
                    <l>Upon the mighty hill, forlorn,</l>
                    <l>He stood alone amid the storm ;</l>
                    <l>Watching the last day&#x2010;gleams decay,</l> 
                    <l>Supposing its returning ray</l>
                    <l>Should see him lying there asleep,</l>
                    <l>With <geogName corresp="#ALPS">Alpine</geogName> snow for winding&#x2010;sheet</l> 
                    <l>Methinks I see him, as he stood</l>
                    <l>Upon the ridge of snow ;</l>
                    <l>The battering burst of winds above,&#x2014;</l> 
                    <l>The cloudy precipice below,&#x2014;</l>
                    <l>Watching the dawn. With proud delight</l> 
                    <l>He saw that long, tempestuous night</l> 
                    <l>Drive to the westward, and unfold</l> 
                    <l>The ocean snow&#x2010;fields, upward rolled,</l> 
                    <l>Bright with the morning&#x02BC;s glance of gold.</l> 
                    <l>It past away,&#x2014; the tossing flood</l>                                                 
                                                
                    <l>Of changing vapour, headlong riding ;</l> 
                    <l>And lo ! the untrodden summit stood</l>
                    <l>Accessibly beside him.</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
